President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of Montana due to flooding that occurred between May 1 and June 10, 2018. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The counties of Carbon, Custer, Golden Valley, Lewis and Clark, Missoula, Musselshell, Park, Powell, and Treasure are eligible for this funding. Hazard mitigation measures will also be supported on a cost-sharing basis throughout the state. James R. Stephenson has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.